02e6767e-ad77-4a30-9cfc-f232ebb328dd.0ec52c7f-178c-4b88-8dc0-53be5c84d538.prompt=FileName\: 02e6767e-ad77-4a30-9cfc-f232ebb328dd.1e91fce0-d7a7-448c-a1b4-928b8baf44fc.description=
Writes the data from "contents" input to the requested file. The operation can be used to overwrite existing content of the file,  append extra lines to it or even create a new file.

Input Parameters\:
file                - Full path to file (can be a UNC path, will attempt to create directory structure). If the file does not exist it is created first.
contents       - The contents to write to the file. Contents can have a new line delimiter which is also given as input to the operation, but it is optional. Example\: "This is line no. 01\nThis is line no. 2\n" where \n is the delimiter.
user              - Username to use for thread impersonation on the RAS host for this operation.
password      - Password for the user.
delimiter        - Specifies the newline delimiter (\n, \r\n, etc) that is used for the "contents" input.
overwrite      - Specifies whether to overwrite the file or append to it. By default, the used value is true. Accepted values\: true, false or the empty string. If this is left empty, the file will be overwritten.
characterSet - The character encoding used to write to the file. The default is UTF-8. Example values\: windows-1252, UTF-16, UTF-16BE,  ISO-8859-1, US-ASCII, Shift_JIS etc.

Responses\:
success - The contents were written to the file.
failure - The operation did not succeed in writing the contents to file.
02e6767e-ad77-4a30-9cfc-f232ebb328dd.2284c916-5944-4105-a695-5b533b7dd46d.description=
Checks to see if a list contains every element in another list.

Inputs\:
sublist -The contained list.
container - The containing list.
delimiter - A delimiter separating elements in the two lists.
ignoreCase - If set to 'True' then the compare is not case sensitive. Default is True

Responses\:
true - sublist is contained in container.
false - sublist is not contained in container.

Results\:
Result - All items contained in the sublist that are not in the container.
02e6767e-ad77-4a30-9cfc-f232ebb328dd.311a7bb7-44b5-4035-94bb-cc864edf420c.description=
Adds a value into the global context (available to all parent and child flows)

Input Parameters\:
keyName - the name of the context variable to use
myValue - the value to assign the context variable

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Scriptlet Example\:
[$scriptletContext putGlobal\: $keyName, $myValue];

02e6767e-ad77-4a30-9cfc-f232ebb328dd.5d8aac84-a366-4031-9cfa-68f49b3d0cf7.description=Check to see if the value stored in a specified key is null. Inputs\: keyName - the key to check Responses\: isNull - if the key is a null pointer. notNull - if some value is stored in the key. 02e6767e-ad77-4a30-9cfc-f232ebb328dd.b297cde1-30e0-4d24-8483-13f093c0e623.description=Iterates through a list of values.If the list changes while running, the updates will be appended to the list. Inputs\: list - The list to iterate through. separator - A delimiter that separates elements in the list. Returns\: The current element of the list, if the response is has more Responses\: has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned. has no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list. failure - failed to process the list. Note\: Where the iterator is in the list is tracked by each step's unique id. Therefore you can iterate on the same list from multiple steps simultaneously. WARNING\: Any step that will use the results of this Iterator operation will, by default, attempt to assign that step's inputs from a flow variable. If this is left checked, then the first element of the iterator will be used for every cycle of iteration.. 02e6767e-ad77-4a30-9cfc-f232ebb328dd.b3b23f3c-2266-440c-b355-0ffae3958bc0.description=
Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults".

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);
02e6767e-ad77-4a30-9cfc-f232ebb328dd.bf009f17-992f-4e85-9c3c-1cf26161acf6.description=
Reads the file specified in the source input parameter.  If Store is true, then all matching lines are pushed into the Session and then subsequent calls to the operation results in the next line being returned.

Inputs\:
source - Path to the file to be read.
filter - Regular expression filter to be applied to each line (can be left blank for all).
store - Whether to store results in the session for retrieval. Valid values \: true,false
delimiter - If set to null, the file is read line by line, otherwise it is a delimiter placed between read lines (note, the entire file may or may not still be fully read at once, depending on size).
user - Username to use for thread impersonation on the RAS host when reading.
password - Password for the user.
eofReset - If set to true than after the No More response has been returned once, the operation will restart reading the file from the beginning on the next call.
characterSet - The character encoding used to read the file (for instance, windows-1252). The default is UTF-8.

Responses\:
more lines - More lines are available to be read in the session.
no more lines - No lines are available for reading in the session.
failure - If something went wrong. 

Results\:
returnResult - One line read from the file. 
COUNT - On the first pass, the total number of lines matched.  On subsequent runs, the number of lines remaining in the session. This result is only returned in line-by-line mode.
02e6767e-ad77-4a30-9cfc-f232ebb328dd.ce045ba6-5973-42dc-ab21-e53eb3bb99e6.description=
Retrieves a value from a list.

Inputs\:
list - A list to get the value from.
delimiter - the delimiter that separates values in the list.
index - the index of the value (Starting at 0) to retrieve from the list, or end for the last element, or end-1 for the second to last element.

Responses\:
success - The operation completed successfully.
failure - Something went wrong.

Returns\:
The value read from the list.
02e6767e-ad77-4a30-9cfc-f232ebb328dd.ced83652-af92-443a-afbd-93cda0ab1ee2.prompt=FileName\: 02e6767e-ad77-4a30-9cfc-f232ebb328dd.d6dd293e-b35a-42ca-a3c9-a5e960a5c3e2.description=
This is an operation that does nothing, and can be used to display information to the user by editing the display tab. It can also be used for filtering flow variables by feeding them in as inputs, and filtering them on the results tab.

Inputs\:
field1 - optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
field2 - optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
field3 - optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
field4 - optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.

Responses\:
success - this operation never fails.
02e6767e-ad77-4a30-9cfc-f232ebb328dd.description=
Updates properties in a properties file with new values. Properties that are not present in the properties file will be ignored.

Inputs\:
properties - A delimiter delimited list of the properties to set. Each property must be in the form name\=value. For example,  myName\=myValue1,myName2\=myValue2
delimiter - The delimiter separating properties. Default is ",".
source - The properties file to update.
characterSet - The character encoding used to read and write to the file (for instance,"utf-16" for utf-16 little endian with BOM). The default is "utf-8".

Responses\:
success - Properties updated successfully.
failure - Something went wrong.

NOTE\:
Make sure that if the characterSet input has one of the following values\: "utf-16", "unicodeFFFE", "utf-32", "utf-32BE", the source file contains BOM at the beginning of the first line. Also make sure the system can handle the characterSet.
